cs.CG, cs.MS, cs.MM, cs.DS, cs.GR

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with generating microstructural geometries using a formalism of Wang tiles, which involves computational geometry techniques.
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is also likely as the paper describes modifications to an existing algorithm for generating microstructural samples.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possibility as the paper includes illustrations of two- and three-dimensional examples.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper involves designing a connectivity graph of a tile set.
- cs.GR (Graphics) is a possibility as the paper deals with generating complex three-dimensional morphologies.
